<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Since this has become more of an issue of late, I'll add my 2cp to this post....<P>No, I do not think that Druids should get a Permenent Charm spell. I think that things are fine the way they are. Here are my reasons:<P>1) This is the most important point...NO other class has a Permenent Charm. Even Enchanters who have the best charms out there still face an occasional unpredictable moment when using charm. Issuing one to Druids would just start a class envy war with Enchanters and Shamans who can both charm.<P>2) Druids are powerful enough with out pets. Does anyone even use one regularly? I use it when I am screwing around, but really it is a waste of time, and for all you guys using them to hunt, you do realize that using a pet takes away a fraction of you own xp when you solo don't you?<P>3) there aren't any Animals in dungeons anyway..this is about the only place I would "like" to use this spell, and in Kunark lands and Dungeons all over..There simply aren't any animals. I'd rather see some more "indoor" spells, not permenent pets.<P>Now, so you have read my comments and you are now saying "Wanderer, you have a few good points, but I'm not convinced and still want my PET!" (well that is what I hope you are saying, not SHUT UP YOU STUPID @$$!). Here are my tips for using Charmed pets...and one for the guy who was complaing that he can't beat up a Necro.<P>When using ANY Charm spells, the MOST important thing to have is a high CHR. If you are seriously going to use a pet all the time, buy some DrakeScale leggings, a Crude Stein, Plat Cat eye Necklace, Plat Star Ruby Veil, ect. The items I just listed give about +50 CHR all together (ok, i might be a little off, but you get the idea). The higher your CHR the less chance of the charmed animal breaking the spell. Next tip, DON'T charm anything you can't kill by yourself. Don't charm a high blue or yellow, go for the Greens and low blues...Reason, if your  charm breaks, you will want to be able to take out the ex-pet without using any mana, also the low blues and greens resist much less, stay charmed longer on average, and will even sometimes run when Charm breaks. Also keep Root or Terrozie Animal ready to give yourself some time to react just in case.<P>As to attacking Necros...NEVER BOTHER WITH THE NECRO'S PET! Forget the pet, Root it, and seperate the Necro form the pet. If you waste any more mana than a Root on a Necro Pet, the Necro will win. Necros are NOT going to be able to Melee with you, they can DoT and blast you a bit...BUT SO CAN YOU! If you do not seperate that pet from the master then you will die, even if you have a pet. Necros are TOTALLY dependant on the pet to protect them in a battle, they have about 1/2 the hp's you do, if you get close to the Necro he will die. You must think of this for each class you fight. When you fight a Warrior I hope you Kite him, When you fight a Wizard you better Melee, ect. Do just jump in there without a plan and expect to win, a player character is 1000% smarter than any NPC, even the 'stupid' players.<P>Wanderer
</FONT>
