<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Lets start by answering the questions about the pet.  Who the hell wants one.  They do nothing but get in your way and suck your mana and exp.  Not to mention get you involved into **** you didn't want to be involved in.  I used my charm spell alot in the emerald jungle.  Charmed apes, tigers, raptors, and leaches.. (yes i said leaches).  I would then park the pet. pull something to it.. and let it battle.  Never helping the pet in the battle at all.. But watching his life as well as the mob's life.   Snare the mob.  When both get low I cancel the magic on the pet.  Snare the pet.. run ahead a little.. Dot both mobs and cast terroize animal.  Bam.. both dotted.. both feared and just standing there taking full damage from my dot.  Both drop.. 2 exp.. very little mana used. <P>As for dueling.. hehe Well druids aren't duelers.. that is for sure. Wanderer was right about somethings and wrong about the others.  A necro and a mage without pet = owned.  Let's face it.. Necros and mages just suck without a pet.  Root the pet.. and blast the necro or mage.  Don't melee.. I repeat.. Don't melee.  A half smart necro or mage would just sit by there pet so melee is futile.   Root. pet.. Root necro/mage.. (pending on your level)  dot and sit down outside of his casting range. Wash, rinse, repeat.  Oh ya.. if the necro lays his pussy dot on you.. Cast a cholro(if high enough)  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">.. by by dot. <P>Wizzies are a little different pending on their level.  Wizzie's do high damage but have high cast times.. and not very high hp.   Ok.. so how to beat the hell out of a wizzie that casts ice commet.  Once again.. melee is not a really good option for a druid.  Even if you hit the wiz.. his spell may still go off and now you have wasted valuable time.   First thing any wiz is going to do is click on his staff to lower your magic resistance.  Then he is going to try and stun ya.  This is the tough part.  If he stuns you he has close to 8 seconds to cast.  If he doesn't stun you .. he is dead.. you cast 2 spells and only take one hit from the IC.. Calefaction which does 440 hp in 2.5 seconds.. and Starfire or Ice which is a 612 dd in 6.2 seconds.   There are many easy ways to beat a wizzie.  <P>Tactic 2.  Bind in zone somewhere. away from melee point.  Dot wizzie.. Gate.  not in spell range now.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">... head back.. wash rinse repeat.. (with track a wizzie has no chance of seeing you coming).   Don't blind you target either.. most casters have their spells  hot keyed.  <P>Fighting melee classes.. 2 ways.. one not so safe and the other safe.  Rangers can be tough to melee cause they root and dispell.  Stack your buffs properly and no dispell will remove your good buffs.   Porcupine at all times.. A Ranger doesn't do great amounts of damage.. The hit for lower amounts but do hit alot faster..   My dmg shield does 29 per hit..  Unless he dispells me alot he is not getting rid of it.. and while he is wasting time on trying. i am rooting and blasting him to death. <BR> Warriors are same way.. But they do more damage then rangers.. so tactic one is not recomended.. .. Kite the warrior.. Their High M.R will help them.. but you will win in the long run.  <P>Remember, there is no such thing as a straight up fight.  You are not a coward for using good tactics to kill your opponent.  They will be pissed off cause they didn't think of it first. <P>BTW.. necros, mages, druids, enchanters.. all can solo.. <P>Keaian Wolvespaw<BR>Wanderer<P>(it's just a game people  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">)
</FONT>
