I think a pet would be a great idea.  Why not?  Druids are masters of nature.  Sheesh we get a spell around 50+ that changes weather.  It goes along the lines of playing a character like a druid.  Druids are part of nature and they should have a pet.  The charm (from what i understand) when it wears off, the creature then attacks.  Never have used it.  A druid should have a animal companion...maybe not until higher levels.  But that would go along with who and what a druid is.  For me it is from a roleplaying perspective..not a power perspective.  The pet does not have to be invincible or overly powerful.  Just something that is a friend and protector to the druid.  I don't have much time to post more on this right now...at work...but will come up with some rules regarding this....maybe one animal for a certain period(or just one, period!)..when it dies you need a rezz or something...something along those lines...if anyone else can think of something else go for it.<P>------------------<BR>Lonewoulf<BR>Protectorate and member of the Guardians of Dawn<BR>Lanys server
