Ok... Here's my take on how this SHOULD work. I know that other classes would b*tch and moan if we got a perm pet, but look at it this way... That sort of thing IS part of what a druid is, thank you Mr. Lonewolf! Why not make it as part of the druid's specialties? Monks get all sorts of special attacks indigenous to ONLY monks... No one complains about that? Paladins can lay on hands, Bards have their songs - rouges can sneak, hide, backstab, make poison, etc. You get the point. WE have NO real special skill that is just ours! In fact EVERY class should have something that makes that class truly unique to the others, variety is the spice of life! For example Necros should be able to summon a skeleton (strengthwise according to level) without eating up any mana for maybe a certain duration? What i'm getting at is that charming/summoning a perm pet should be OUR special thing. No one says that the pet has to be rediculously strong. It can be made so that (again) you can obtain a pet in accordance to your level so that nothing gets out of hand... say - equal to or less than your level. Creatures should be anywhere from wolves, bears, cat family and possibly some spiders? Maybe griffins WAY, WAY down the road...
