Missing my point.  I am not asking for a pet for a weapon.  Not everything in this world has to deal with attack/kill/loot.  Roleplaying is a big part of it.  Yes you can have fun and roleplay.  People who spend their time just camping and looting are going to get bored with this game.  Ref: Diablo II.<BR>If all I wanted out of it was a weapon then charm is where i would go.  But like I said, I don't use it.  I role play the druid as a friend of nature.  I do not use the creature to fight a battle.  If it is attacking me then all bets are off...lions, griffawns, griffeenes, griffins, gorge hounds, etc.  If you have a pet as a druid then let it be a few levels lower then you.  When you are attacked it automatically attacks the creature beating on you unless you call it off.  If the creature dies then let there be a certain time period between each pet...that  way a druid would think twice about throwing his pet into the fray.  The pet could be used say as a scout for the druid or the party he is in.  Yeah it sounds complicated, but hey creativity is the name of the game (or sorta).  Pets could be like the druid in wolfform.....cons indifferent...until it attacks.  Maybe once a month in game time a druid is allowed a pet...and that pet also has to gain exp...naaaaah way to complicated on the exp thing.  But the pet is a few levels under the druid and the creature eventually can not exceed a certain level...say 20 - 25 or even less maybe 10-15.  It is from the roleplaying perspective that i am looking at this.  Once again just my humble opinion. <BR>Roleplaying is essential to the life of this game.  Otherwise it is just another quake/doom/diablo.<P>------------------<BR>Lonewoulf<BR>Protectorate and member of the Guardians of Dawn<BR>Lanys server
