<FONT SIZE="1" color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted July 28, 2000 04:02 PM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=56&t=000005&reply_num=000034&u="><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=56&t=000005&replyto=000034"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
To answer all questions on this subject once and for all for those of you who don't think that druids should be able to charm/befriend a pet. No one says that you necessarily HAVE to use one? Just like the fact that not every person that plays a class that have pets use them... It's a preference! The thing here is that you SHOULD have the option to take one on if you like. Druid are akin with nature and ALL of it's creatures. For anyone familiar with what a druid truly is in terms of the fantasy/roleplaying genre, animals are considered equals as well as friends to a druid. Therefore, why WOULDN'T a druid be able to have a pet friend? Take the relationship between you and your dog and apply it to druids. Your dog cons you amiably (In most cases) Some dogs will even try to protect their owner/friend from certain perceived dangers. Well, druids are just on a higher level than that and are the friend of most beast... In fact, I think that we should con amiably to the cat family! (Lions, panthers, etc.) Not every druid in the world may want a pet, but i'm sure many do. And I STILL stand by the fact that it makes sense for a druid to befriend animals whether we really need them or not!
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
